   <p conkeyref="setClientRole1/desc"/>
   <p>If you call this method to switch the user role after joining the channel, the SDK triggers the following callbacks:<ul>
       <li>The callback is triggered locally<xref keyref="IChannel_onClientRoleChanged"/>.</li>
       <li>Remote trigger<xref keyref="IChannel_onUserJoined"/> or<xref keyref="IChannel_onUserOffline"/> callback.</li>
   </ul></p>
   <note outputclass="note">
       <ul>
       <li>This method only takes effect when the channel scene is live broadcast (<xref keyref="setChannelProfile"/>the middle <parmname>profile</parmname> is set to <ph keyref="CHANNEL_PROFILE_LIVE_BROADCASTING"/>).</li>
       <li>The difference between this method and<xref keyref="IChannel_setClientRole1"/> [1/2] is that this method also supports setting user levels.<ul conkeyref="setClientRole2/diff"><li/></ul>
       </li>
       </ul>
       </note>
